$ Excel: Data -> Get & Transform Data -> Existing Connections

*Data -> Existing Connections* opens the *Existing Connections dialog* which shows all connections that are currently available and all
→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/table[Excel table] in the current → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook.

{ Tabs
  { Connections

    The *Connections* tab shows connections
      • in this workbook
      • on the network
      • on this computer (`.odc` (and other?) files)

    { Browse for more… #xls_existing-connections_browse-for-more

      *Browse for more* opens → Windows/dirs/Users/username/Documents/My-Data-Sources[`C:\Users\username\Documents\My Data Sources`].

    }

  }
  { Tables

    The *Tables* tab shows → Microsoft/Office/Excel/table[Excel Tables].

  }

}
sa:

  The object → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/WorkbookConnection[`workbookConnection`]

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel#xls-connecting-to-data-sources[Connecting to data sources from Excel]

  The → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/QueryTable#queryTable-connection[`connection`] property of the → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/QueryTable[`QueryTable` Excel Object].
